'final' Keyword (Constants & Restriction) ğŸš«
ğŸ§  Logic:final keyword ka upyog kisi entity ko constant ya restrict (pratibandhit) karne ke liye kiya jata hai. Iske teen mukhya upyog hain:Final Variable: Value set hone ke baad badli nahi ja sakti (constant ban jata hai).Final Method: Is method ko override nahi kiya ja sakta (Inheritance mein).Final Class: Is class ko inherit nahi kiya ja sakta (koi aur class ise extends nahi kar sakti).ğŸ“Œ Example:Java// Final Variable
final double PI = 3.14159; // Constant value

class Parent {
    final void display() {
        System.out.println("Final method.");
    }
}

class Child extends Parent {
    // void display() { } // ERROR! Final method cannot be overridden
}
ğŸ”¤ Java Code:Javafinal class BaseVehicle { // Is class ko inherit nahi kiya ja sakta
    public void start() {
        System.out.println("Base Vehicle started.");
    }
}

class Constants {
    // Conventionally, final static variables are ALL_CAPS
    public static final int MAX_USERS = 100; 
}

public class FinalKeywordDemo {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        // Final variable
        final int LIMIT = 50;
        // LIMIT = 60; // ERROR! Cannot reassign final variable
        
        System.out.println("Limit: " + LIMIT); // 50
        System.out.println("Max Users: " + Constants.MAX_USERS); // 100
        
        // Example: BaseVehicle ko inherit nahi kiya ja sakta.
        // class Truck extends BaseVehicle { } // Compilation Error
    }
}
